            verseRef = "Romans 8:6",
            text = "Heavenly Father, as I open my eyes to this new day, I am conscious of the battle for my mind. There is a constant pull toward the 'flesh'—toward worry, or pride, or resentment, or self-centeredness. I know that path leads to a kind of internal death. But I am asking for Your Spirit to govern my thoughts today, because I desperately want the 'life and peace' that only You can provide.\n\nSet my mind on the things above. When a negative thought enters my head, help me to catch it and replace it with Your truth. When I am tempted to dwell on a past mistake or a future fear, redirect my focus to Your present grace. I want my mind to be a sanctuary of Your presence, a place where Your Word is the final authority. Help me to filter everything I hear and see through the lens of the Gospel.\n\nI surrender my imagination, my logic, and my internal dialogue to You. May my 'default' thought pattern be one of gratitude and trust. Give me the mental discipline to stay focused on what is pure, lovely, and admirable. I am choosing to believe that I have the 'mind of Christ.' Let that reality shape my attitudes, my words, and my actions throughout this entire day. I am walking in life and peace because Your Spirit is in control.",
