            verse = "The Lord said to him, 'Who gave human beings their mouths? Who makes them deaf or mute? Who gives them sight or makes them blind? Is it not I, the Lord? Now go; I will help you speak and will teach you what to say.'",
            verseRef = "Exodus 4:11-12",
            text = "Lord, I am starting this day feeling incredibly small and completely inadequate for the tasks ahead of me. I look at my own abilities, my own resources, and my own experience, and I see nothing but gaps. Like Moses, my 'speech is slow' and my 'confidence is low.' I am tempted to shrink back and ask You to send someone else—anyone else—who is more qualified.\n\nBut I thank You for the reminder that You are the Creator of the mouth, the eye, and the ear. You don't call the qualified; You qualify the called. My inadequacy is not an obstacle to Your power; it is the very platform for it. Help me to stop looking at what I *don't* have and to start looking at who *is* with me. You have promised that You will help me speak and that You will teach me what to say. You have promised that Your grace is sufficient for my weakness.\n\nI step out into this day not in my own strength, but in Your sufficiency. If I fail, let it be in Your name. If I succeed, let it be for Your glory. I am choosing to believe that You have provided everything I need for exactly where You have placed me. I am not enough, but You are more than enough. Go before me, stand beside me, and work through me today. I am Your instrument.",
