            verseRef = "Psalm 61:2",
            text = "Heavenly Father, I am starting this day with a heart that feels faint and a mind that feels crowded. The demands on my time, the weight of my responsibilities, and the uncertainty of my future are pressing in on me from every side. I feel like I am standing on shifting sand, struggling to stay upright in a rising tide. I need the 'Rock that is higher than I.'\n\nLead me out of my own small perspective and into the vastness of Your sovereignty. Remind me that nothing is too big for You to handle and nothing is too small for You to care about. When I look at my to-do list, help me to see Your potential rather than my own pressure. Give me the grace to take one step at a time, trusting that You are providing the strength for exactly what I need right now. I don't need to see the whole path; I just need to hold Your hand.\n\nI surrender my 'overwhelmed' feelings to You. Replace my panic with Your peace. Quiet the internal noise that tells me I have to be everywhere and do everything. You are my refuge and my strong tower. I am choosing to stand on the Rock of Your faithfulness today. I may be faint, but You are firm. I may be weary, but You are wonderful. Lead me, Lord.",
