            text = "Lord Jesus, I want my first act of the day to be an act of love. You have said that the best way I can show my love for You is through my obedience to Your Word. I don't want to just 'know' Your commands; I want to 'keep' them. I want my life to be a practical demonstration of my devotion to You. Give me a heart that is sensitive to the leading of Your Spirit and quick to respond to Your truth.\n\nShow me the areas where I am tempted to compromise—where I prioritize my convenience over Your call, or my reputation over Your righteousness. Give me the courage to say 'No' to the things that grieve Your heart and 'Yes' to the things that reflect Your glory. I want to be someone who is 'all in' for the Kingdom. Help me to view obedience not as a burden to be borne, but as a path to be enjoyed. It is the path where I experience Your presence most clearly.\n\nAs I interact with others today, may my obedience to the command to 'love your neighbor' be evident. May my integrity in my work be an act of worship. I am choosing to follow You, not out of duty, but out of deep, transformative love. You are my Master and my Friend. I am Yours, and I am ready to obey.",
