            verseRef = "Matthew 6:6",
            text = "Heavenly Father, I am beginning this day by 'closing the door.' Before I engage with the demands of the world, before I seek the approval of others, and before I perform for any audience, I want to be alone with You. I am seeking the 'secret place' of Your presence. I want to be fueled by the 'unseen' reality of Your love before I face the 'seen' challenges of my life.\n\nThank You that You 'see what is done in secret.' You see the quiet surrender, the honest confession, and the desperate trust that no one else witnessed. I don't need a platform; I just need a Person. I don't need a public reward; I need a private renewal. Strengthen my internal man today. Deepen my roots in the soil of Your grace. May my public life be the natural overflow of my private intimacy with You. I want to be the same person in the crowd that I am in the closet.\n\nProtect the 'secret place' of my heart throughout this day. When the noise of the world gets loud, help me to retreat to that internal room where You are waiting. I am not living for the applause of men; I am living for the smile of my Father. You are my priority, my provision, and my peace. I am starting from the secret, and I am going into the strength. You are my Reward.",
