            title = "A Morning Prayer for a Heart for the Lost",
            verse = "I tell you that in the same way there will be more rejoicing in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need to repent.",
            verseRef = "Luke 15:7",
            text = "Lord Jesus, I want to start this day with Your heart for the 'one.' It's so easy to focus on the 'ninety-nine'—on the people who are like me, the people who agree with me, and the people who make my life comfortable. Give me the eyes to see those who are lost, those who are wandering, and those who feel forgotten by the world. I want my heart to beat in sync with the rejoicing of Heaven.\n\nBreak my heart for what breaks Yours. Help me to notice the person who is struggling behind a smile, the neighbor who is isolated, and the coworker who is searching for meaning. Use me as a vessel of Your searching love today. Give me the courage to reach out, the wisdom to speak truth, and the patience to listen. I don't want to just 'do church'; I want to be Your hands and feet in the world. I want to be part of the rescue.\n\nMay my life be a pointer to the Good Shepherd. Let my kindness be a bridge and my story be an invitation. I refuse to be a 'righteous person who doesn't need to repent' in my own eyes. I am a rescued sinner, and I want to help others find the way Home. Fill me with Your compassion today. Let's go find the lost ones together.",
